HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 195
BY REPRESENTATIVE FREIBERG
A RESOLUTION
To designate Monday, April 27, 2026, as Louisiana Young Heroes Day at the state capitol
and to commend the Louisiana Public Broadcasting 2026 Louisiana Young Heroes.
WHEREAS, Louisiana Public Broadcasting (LPB) defines a "Young Hero" as an
exceptional young person who has excelled in academics, given significantly of themselves
through public service, overcome personal adversity, exhibited extraordinary heroism, or
inspired others through their deeds and strength of character to become better students,
people, and citizens; and
WHEREAS, LPB honors seven high school students from around the state as the
2026 Louisiana Young Heroes; these outstanding students are role models in their local
communities and will join over two hundred thirty-six past honorees who have received this
award during the program's thirty-year history; and
WHEREAS, Jaden Armstrong of Baton Rouge is a senior at Liberty Magnet High
School; he is a problem solver and entrepreneur who developed his own clothing brand, Feel
Better, which incorporates braille; he is inspired by his visually-impaired younger brother
and was among the top six finalists at the Young Entrepreneurs Academy national
competition; and
WHEREAS, Marleigh Auzenne of Lafayette is a sophomore at Early College
Academy; she has a nonverbal autistic brother who inspired her to create the Sound
Sanctuary Noise-Cancelling Headphone Lending Library for people with sensory needs; she
also serves as a junior facilitator for The Confidence Campaign of Acadiana's Girl
Empowerment Workshops; and
